Hey Derek,

I'm hoping to get a paper submitted there.  

What are the eye's motions like when looking over fingerprints?  It 
would be really interesting to see movies of the the eye examining a 
fingerprint. 

ken

--- In neat@yahoogroups.com, Derek James <djames@g...> wrote:
> Just wondering if anybody else on this list is planning on 
attending
> GECCO 2005 in Washington DC.  Philip and I are planning on 
attending,
> and we're hoping to submit a paper for the regular paper deadline 
in
> mid-January.
> 
> We're working on fingerprint classification now, automatically
> categorizing fingerprints into one of four classes: whorl, left 
loop,
> right loop, or arch (and for the five-class problem, tented arch). 
> Automatic classification of fingerprints is a pretty difficult
> problem, and is hard to do quickly and accurately.
> 
> We're in the early stages of experimenting in this domain, but 
we've
> already evolved a network that can distinguish two distinct left 
loop
> prints from two of each of the other classes, so we're pretty
> optimistic.
> 
> Derek
